.TH "ti_sci_reset_status" 9 "ti_sci_reset_status" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ti_sci_reset_status \- check device reset status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ti_sci_reset_status
.BI "(struct reset_controller_dev *rcdev "  ","
.BI "unsigned long id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rcdev" 12
reset controller entity
.IP "id" 12
ID of reset to be checked
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function implements the reset driver op to return the status of a
device's reset using the TI SCI protocol. The reset register value is read
by invoking the TI SCI device operation .\fBget_device_resets\fP, and the
status of the specific reset is extracted and returned using this reset's
reset mask.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if reset is deasserted, or a non-zero value if reset is asserted
